canonical:
  title: 遣興
  author: 朴宜中
  language: lzh
  text: 節序忽云暮客行何所之一身長作梗雙鬢已成絲短帽風聲緊踈燈夜影遲昨非今始覺事事不如期
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 遣興
  author: 朴宜中
  language: lzh
  text: 節序忽云暮。客行何所之。一身長作梗。雙鬢已成絲。短帽風聲緊。踈燈夜影遲。昨非今始覺。事事不如期。
korean:
  title: 견흥
  author: 박의중
  language: kor
  text: |-
    시절이 어느덧 저물었는데
    나그네는 어디를 갈까
    한 몸은 길이 떠도는 신세
    뒤 귀밑은 이미 흰 실이 되었네
    짧은 모자에는 바람소리가 세차고
    성긴 등잔불에는 밤 그림자가 더디네
    어제의 잘못을 오늘에야 비로소 깨닫노니
    모든 일은 다 기대하던 것과 같지 않네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0130_010_0660&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Idle Musings
  author: Park Ui-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The seasons have slipped away—where does this wanderer go?
    A body adrift, perpetually displaced,
    the hair at my temples already turned to silver thread.

    The wind shrieks through my narrow hat,
    the sparse lamplight casts shadows that linger in the dark.

    Only now do I understand yesterday's mistakes,
    and see that nothing unfolds as I had hoped.
  footnotes:
    - The 'narrow hat' and 'sparse lamplight' evoke both the literal conditions of a traveler's journey and the poet's inner desolation
    - '''Silver thread'' is a classical image for aging, emphasizing the passage of time and loss'
